Pensioner Alan Spencer's life was saved by his 18-month old Labrador Lexi . 
 The 67-year-old began choking on pickled onion and felt life 'slipping away'But Lexi jumped on his back - dislodging the onion and saving his life . 
 An earlier version of this article stated that Lexi the labrador had saved Mr Spencer's live by performing the Heimlich manoeuvre. In fact, the dog jumped on his back to clear the blockage. Heimlich involves applying sudden, strong pressure on the abdomen, which was not the case